Advertise the standard signal range in the AgentOS WASI sysroot.

The patched WASI signal surface exposes conventional non-realtime signal names
through SIGSYS (31) and keeps realtime signal APIs hidden. Report _NSIG as 32 so
portable gnulib-generated headers do not reject the sysroot as a realtime-signal
platform.

diff --git a/libc-top-half/musl/arch/wasm32/bits/signal.h b/libc-top-half/musl/arch/wasm32/bits/signal.h
index 478e1c8..7501d99 100644
--- a/libc-top-half/musl/arch/wasm32/bits/signal.h
+++ b/libc-top-half/musl/arch/wasm32/bits/signal.h
@@ -35,6 +35,6 @@
 #define SIGSYS    31
 #define SIGUNUSED SIGSYS
 
-#define _NSIG 65
+#define _NSIG 32
 
 #endif
